{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Walnut and Rosemary Pastry","content":["Place chopped walnuts, brown sugar, salt, rosemary leaves, flour, butter and egg in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to a floured work surface. Shape pastry into a ball, then flatten into a disc and wrap in cling film. Place in fridge to chill (approx. 30 minutes) until pastry is firm enough to roll. Meanwhile, clean and dry mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 180°C. Set aside 8 individual loose-based tartlet tins (Ø 8 cm).","Place pastry between 2 pieces of baking paper. Roll out thinly (approx. 4 mm thick), dusting with flour as needed to prevent sticking.","Remove top layer of baking paper. Using a round pastry cutter (Ø 10 cm) cut pastry into discs and carefully press into tins. Re-roll pastry and cut out remaining discs to line all tartlet tins (8 in total). Prick bases with a fork and place in fridge for 10 minutes.","Transfer tarts onto a baking tray, line tarts with baking paper, fill with baking beans then bake for 15 minutes (180°C). Remove baking beans and baking paper then bake for 10 minutes (180°C), or until pastry is golden brown. Allow to cool completely before filling. Meanwhile, continue with recipe."]},{"title":"Limoncello Filling and Topping","content":["Place sugar and lemon zest in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>8 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Add limoncello, lemon juice, egg and egg yolks then heat <nobr>8 min\/70°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer sabayon to a large bowl and allow to cool for 15 minutes before placing in fridge for 10 minutes."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place cream in mixing bowl and, without measuring cup and without setting a time, whip <nobr>speed 3<\/nobr> until soft peaks form, watching carefully to avoid over-whipping. Transfer to bowl with sabayon and gently fold together. Fill each pastry case to the top with cream mixture. Refrigerate for one hour. Garnish with fresh figs before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Walnut and Rosemary Pastry","content":["80 g walnuts, chopped","40 g brown sugar","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 Tbsp fresh rosemary, leaves only","230 g wholemeal flour","120 g unsalted butter, diced","1 large egg","wholemeal flour, for dusting"]},{"title":"Limoncello Filling and Topping","content":["80 g sugar","1 Tbsp lemon zest","80 g limoncello","60 g lemon juice, freshly squeezed (1-2 lemons)","1 large egg","4 egg yolks, from large eggs","200 g whipping cream","8 fresh figs, cut in eighths"]}],"id":"r175666","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-RguyKmL2yIo\/XZWp-dyeWPI\/AAAAAAAAfRY\/ShKMOtN0J7cjZjiDwh-Q6u-rkrMEcajTgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_9-PrJ55pjj0STSL1.png","title":"Limoncello Tarts","publishedAt":"2017-08-28T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10 g","fat":"32 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"44 g","calories":"2244 kJ \/ 536 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, cling film, round pastry cutter, fork, baking tray, tartlet tins (Ø 8 cm), rolling pin, baking beans, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Serve the limoncello tarts with seasonal fresh fruit such as strawberries, raspberries or peaches."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","3h 15m","8 portions"]}